TI  - Multinationality and Firm Performance: The Moderating Role of R&D and Marketing Capabilities
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 79
EP  - 97
VL  - 33
IS  - 1
AB  - Researchers in international business have long been interested in understanding the relationship between the multinationality of a firm and its market performance. This article contributes to this research stream by incorporating firm heterogeneity in examining the multinationality-performance relationship. The findings, based on a time series cross-sectional analysis of firms from 12 different industries over a seven-year period, indicate that the impact of multinationality on both financial and operational performance is moderated by firm's R&D and marketing capabilities.
