PY  - 2002
DA  - 2002/03/01
TI  - Corporate International Activity and Debt Financing
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 129
EP  - 147
VL  - 33
IS  - 1
AB  - The literature provides conflicting evidence on the relation between corporate international activity and the cost and level of debt financing. Based on this evidence, we explore the impact of firm internationalization on debt financing. Using a market based sample of U.S. firms, we find significant evidence of a non monotonic relation between firm international activity and both the cost and level of debt financing. Specifically, we find that, contrary to prior research, firm international activity is, on average, associated with a 13% reduction in the cost of debt financing and a 30% increase in firm leverage.
